resource.name: Patient
resource.description: Demographics and other administrative information about an individual or animal receiving care or other health-related services.

property.name: active
property.description: Whether this patient's record is in active use

property.name: name
property.description: A name associated with the patient

property.name: telecom
property.description: A contact detail for the individual

property.name: birthDate
property.description: The date of birth for the individual

property.name: deceased[x]
property.description: Indicates if the individual is deceased or not

property.name: multipleBirth[x]
property.description: Whether patient is part of a multiple birth

property.name: contact
property.description: A contact party (e.g. guardian, partner, friend) for the patient

property.name: communication
property.description: A language which may be used to communicate with the patient about his or her health

property.name: managingOrganization
property.description: Organization that is the custodian of the patient record

property.name: link
property.description: Link to a Patient or RelatedPerson resource that concerns the same actual individual

element.name: Resource
element.description: Base Resource (abstract)

element.name: Element
element.description: Element Type: Base definition for all elements in a resource.

element.name: BackboneElement
element.description: BackboneElement Type: Base definition for all elements that are defined inside a resource - but not those in a data type.

property.name: modifierExtension
property.description: Extensions that cannot be ignored even if unrecognized

element.name: Address
element.description: Address Type: An address expressed using postal conventions (as opposed to GPS or other location definition formats). This data type may be used to convey addresses for use in delivering mail as well as for visiting locations which might not be valid for mail delivery. There are a variety of postal address formats defined around the world. The ISO21090-codedString may be used to provide a coded representation of the contents of strings in an Address.

property.name: use
property.description: home | work | temp | old | billing - purpose of this address

property.name: line
property.description: Street name, number, direction & P.O. Box etc.

property.name: country
property.description: Country (e.g. may be ISO 3166 2 or 3 letter code)

property.name: period
property.description: Time period when address was/is in use

element.name: Age
element.description: Age Type: A duration of time during which an organism (or a process) has existed.

property.name: comparator
property.description: < | <= | >= | > | ad - how to understand the value

property.name: system
property.description: System that defines coded unit form

element.name: Annotation
element.description: Annotation Type: A text note which also contains information about who made the statement and when.

element.name: Attachment
element.description: Attachment Type: For referring to data content defined in other formats.

property.name: contentType

property.name: url

property.name: size

property.name: title
property.description: Label to display in place of the data

property.name: height
property.description: Height of the image in pixels (photo/video)

property.name: width
property.description: Width of the image in pixels (photo/video)

element.name: Availability
element.description: Availability Type: Availability data for an {item}.

property.name: notAvailableTime

element.name: CodeableReference

element.name: Coding
element.description: Coding Type: A reference to a code defined by a terminology system.

property.name: version
property.description: Version of the system - if relevant

property.name: code
property.description: Symbol in syntax defined by the system

property.name: userSelected

element.name: ContactDetail

property.name: name

property.name: telecom

element.name: ContactPoint

property.name: system

property.name: use
property.description: home | work | temp | old | mobile - purpose of this contact point

property.name: rank
property.description: Specify preferred order of use (1 = highest)

property.name: period
property.description: Time period when the contact point was/is in use

element.name: Count
element.description: Count Type: A measured amount (or an amount that can potentially be measured). Note that measured amounts include amounts that are not precisely quantified, including amounts involving arbitrary units and floating currencies.

property.name: comparator

property.name: system

element.name: DataRequirement

property.name: profile

property.name: subject[x]

property.name: mustSupport

element.name: Distance
element.description: Distance Type: A length - a value with a unit that is a physical distance.

property.name: comparator

property.name: system

element.name: Dosage
element.description: Dosage Type: Indicates how the medication is/was taken or should be taken by the patient.

property.name: modifierExtension
property.description: Extensions that cannot be ignored even if unrecognized

property.name: sequence
property.description: The order of the dosage instructions

property.name: text
property.description: Free text dosage instructions e.g. SIG

property.name: additionalInstruction
property.description: Supplemental instruction or warnings to the patient - e.g. "with meals", "may cause drowsiness"

property.name: doseAndRate
property.description: Amount of medication administered, to be administered or typical amount to be administered

property.name: maxDosePerPeriod
property.description: Upper limit on medication per unit of time

property.name: maxDosePerAdministration
property.description: Upper limit on medication per administration

property.name: maxDosePerLifetime
property.description: Upper limit on medication per lifetime of the patient

element.name: Duration
element.description: Duration Type: A length of time.

property.name: comparator
property.description: < | <= | >= | > | ad - how to understand the value

property.name: system
property.description: System that defines coded unit form

element.name: Expression
element.description: Expression Type: A expression that is evaluated in a specified context and returns a value. The context of use of the expression must specify the context in which the expression is evaluated, and how the result of the expression is used.

property.name: description
property.description: Natural language description of the condition

property.name: name
property.description: Short name assigned to expression for reuse

element.name: ExtendedContactDetail
element.description: ExtendedContactDetail Type: Specifies contact information for a specific purpose over a period of time, might be handled/monitored by a specific named person or organization.

property.name: name
property.description: Name of an individual to contact

property.name: organization
property.description: This contact detail is handled/monitored by a specific organization

property.name: period
property.description: Period that this contact was valid for usage

element.name: Extension
element.description: Extension Type: Optional Extension Element - found in all resources.

property.name: url
property.description: identifies the meaning of the extension

element.name: HumanName
element.description: HumanName Type: A name, normally of a human, that can be used for other living entities (e.g. animals but not organizations) that have been assigned names by a human and may need the use of name parts or the need for usage information.

property.name: use
property.description: usual | official | temp | nickname | anonymous | old | maiden

property.name: text
property.description: Text representation of the full name

property.name: given
property.description: Given names (not always 'first'). Includes middle names

property.name: prefix
property.description: Parts that come before the name

property.name: suffix
property.description: Parts that come after the name

property.name: period
property.description: Time period when name was/is in use

element.name: Identifier
element.description: Identifier Type: An identifier - identifies some entity uniquely and unambiguously. Typically this is used for business identifiers.

property.name: use
property.description: usual | official | temp | secondary | old (If known)

property.name: system
property.description: The namespace for the identifier value

property.name: period
property.description: Time period when id is/was valid for use

property.name: assigner
property.description: Organization that issued id (may be just text)

element.name: Meta
element.description: Meta Type: The metadata about a resource. This is content in the resource that is maintained by the infrastructure. Changes to the content might not always be associated with version changes to the resource.

property.name: lastUpdated
property.description: When the resource version last changed

property.name: source
property.description: Identifies where the resource comes from

property.name: profile
property.description: Profiles this resource claims to conform to

property.name: security
property.description: Security Labels applied to this resource

element.name: Money
element.description: Money Type: An amount of economic utility in some recognized currency.

element.name: ParameterDefinition
element.description: ParameterDefinition Type: The parameters to the module. This collection specifies both the input and output parameters. Input parameters are provided by the caller as part of the $evaluate operation. Output parameters are included in the GuidanceResponse.

property.name: name
property.description: Name used to access the parameter value

property.name: documentation
property.description: A brief description of the parameter

property.name: profile
property.description: What profile the value is expected to be

element.name: Period
element.description: Period Type: A time period defined by a start and end date and optionally time.

property.name: end
property.description: End time with inclusive boundary, if not ongoing

element.name: Quantity
element.description: Quantity Type: A measured amount (or an amount that can potentially be measured). Note that measured amounts include amounts that are not precisely quantified, including amounts involving arbitrary units and floating currencies.

property.name: comparator
property.description: < | <= | >= | > | ad - how to understand the value

property.name: system
property.description: System that defines coded unit form

element.name: Range
element.description: Range Type: A set of ordered Quantities defined by a low and high limit.

element.name: Ratio
element.description: Ratio Type: A relationship of two Quantity values - expressed as a numerator and a denominator.

element.name: RatioRange
element.description: RatioRange Type: A range of ratios expressed as a low and high numerator and a denominator.

element.name: Reference
element.description: Reference Type: A reference from one resource to another.

property.name: reference
property.description: Literal reference, Relative, internal or absolute URL

property.name: type
property.description: Type the reference refers to (e.g. "Patient") - must be a resource in resources

property.name: identifier
property.description: Logical reference, when literal reference is not known

element.name: RelatedArtifact
element.description: RelatedArtifact Type: Related artifacts such as additional documentation, justification, or bibliographic references.

property.name: type
property.description: documentation | justification | citation | predecessor | successor | derived-from | depends-on | composed-of | part-of | amends | amended-with | appends | appended-with | cites | cited-by | comments-on | comment-in | contains | contained-in | corrects | correction-in | replaces | replaced-with | retracts | retracted-by | signs | similar-to | supports | supported-with | transforms | transformed-into | transformed-with | documents | specification-of | created-with | cite-as

property.name: display
property.description: Brief description of the related artifact

property.name: resourceReference
property.description: What artifact, if not a conformance resource

property.name: publicationDate
property.description: Date of publication of the artifact being referred to

element.name: SampledData
element.description: SampledData Type: A series of measurements taken by a device, with upper and lower limits. There may be more than one dimension in the data.

property.name: intervalUnit
property.description: The measurement unit of the interval between samples

property.name: factor
property.description: Multiply data by this before adding to origin

property.name: dimensions
property.description: Number of sample points at each time point

property.name: codeMap
property.description: Defines the codes used in the data

property.name: offsets
property.description: Offsets, typically in time, at which data values were taken

property.name: data
property.description: Decimal values with spaces, or "E" | "U" | "L", or another code

element.name: Signature
element.description: Signature Type: A signature along with supporting context. The signature may be a digital signature that is cryptographic in nature, or some other signature acceptable to the domain. This other signature may be as simple as a graphical image representing a hand-written signature, or a signature ceremony Different signature approaches have different utilities.

property.name: type
property.description: Indication of the reason the entity signed the object(s)

property.name: targetFormat
property.description: The technical format of the signed resources

property.name: sigFormat
property.description: The technical format of the signature

property.name: data
property.description: The actual signature content (XML DigSig. JWS, picture, etc.)

element.name: Timing
element.description: Timing Type: Specifies an event that may occur multiple times. Timing schedules are used to record when things are planned, expected or requested to occur. The most common usage is in dosage instructions for medications. They are also used when planning care of various kinds, and may be used for reporting the schedule to which past regular activities were carried out.

property.name: modifierExtension
property.description: Extensions that cannot be ignored even if unrecognized

property.name: repeat
property.description: When the event is to occur

property.name: code
property.description: C | BID | TID | QID | AM | PM | QD | QOD | +

element.name: TriggerDefinition
element.description: TriggerDefinition Type: A description of a triggering event. Triggering events can be named events, data events, or periodic, as determined by the type element.

property.name: type
property.description: named-event | periodic | data-changed | data-added | data-modified | data-removed | data-accessed | data-access-ended

property.name: name
property.description: Name or URI that identifies the event

element.name: UsageContext
element.description: UsageContext Type: Specifies clinical/business/etc. metadata that can be used to retrieve, index and/or categorize an artifact. This metadata can either be specific to the applicable population (e.g., age category, DRG) or the specific context of care (e.g., venue, care setting, provider of care).

codeset.name: AdministrativeGender
codeset.description: The gender of a person used for administrative purposes.

code.name: Male
code.description: Male.

code.name: Female
code.description: Female.

code.name: Other
code.description: Other.

code.name: Unknown
code.description: Unknown.

codeset.name: PropertyRepresentation
codeset.description: How a property is represented when serialized.

code.name: XML Attribute
code.description: In XML, this property is represented as an attribute not an element.

code.name: XML Text
code.description: This element is represented using the XML text attribute (primitives only).

code.name: Type Attribute
code.description: The type of this element is indicated using xsi:type.

code.name: CDA Text Format
code.description: Use CDA narrative instead of XHTML.

code.name: XHTML
code.description: The property is represented using XHTML.

codeset.name: ConstraintSeverity
codeset.description: SHALL applications comply with this constraint?

code.name: Error
code.description: If the constraint is violated, the resource is not conformant.

code.name: Warning
code.description: If the constraint is violated, the resource is conformant, but it is not necessarily following best practice.

codeset.name: QuantityComparator
codeset.description: How the Quantity should be understood and represented.

code.name: Less than
code.description: The actual value is less than the given value.

code.name: Less or Equal to
code.description: The actual value is less than or equal to the given value.

code.name: Greater or Equal to
code.description: The actual value is greater than or equal to the given value.

code.name: Greater than
code.description: The actual value is greater than the given value.

code.name: Sufficient to achieve this total quantity
code.description: The actual value is sufficient for the total quantity to equal the given value.

codeset.name: PriceComponentType
codeset.description: Codes indicating the kind of the price component.

code.name: base price
code.description: the amount is the base price used for calculating the total price before applying surcharges, discount or taxes.

code.name: surcharge
code.description: the amount is a surcharge applied on the base price.

code.name: deduction
code.description: the amount is a deduction applied on the base price.

code.name: discount
code.description: the amount is a discount applied on the base price.

code.name: tax
code.description: the amount is the tax component of the total price.

code.name: informational
code.description: the amount is of informational character, it has not been applied in the calculation of the total price.

codeset.name: ContactPointUse
codeset.description: Use of contact point.

code.name: Home
code.description: A communication contact point at a home; attempted contacts for business purposes might intrude privacy and chances are one will contact family or other household members instead of the person one wishes to call. Typically used with urgent cases, or if no other contacts are available.

code.name: Work
code.description: An office contact point. First choice for business related contacts during business hours.

code.name: Temp
code.description: A temporary contact point. The period can provide more detailed information.

code.name: Old
code.description: This contact point is no longer in use (or was never correct, but retained for records).

code.name: Mobile
code.description: A telecommunication device that moves and stays with its owner. May have characteristics of all other use codes, suitable for urgent matters, not the first choice for routine business.

codeset.name: BindingStrength
codeset.description: Indication of the degree of conformance expectations associated with a binding.

code.name: Required
code.description: To be conformant, the concept in this element SHALL be from the specified value set.

code.name: Extensible
code.description: To be conformant, the concept in this element SHALL be from the specified value set if any of the codes within the value set can apply to the concept being communicated. If the value set does not cover the concept (based on human review), alternate codings (or, data type allowing, text) may be included instead.

code.name: Preferred
code.description: Instances are encouraged to draw from the specified codes for interoperability purposes but are not required to do so to be considered conformant.

code.name: Example
code.description: Instances are not expected or even encouraged to draw from the specified value set. The value set merely provides examples of the types of concepts intended to be included.

codeset.name: AdditionalBindingPurposeCodes
codeset.description: Additional Binding Purpose

code.name: Maximum Binding
code.description: A required binding, for use when the binding strength is 'extensible' or 'preferred'

code.name: Minimum Binding
code.description: The minimum allowable value set - any conformant system SHALL support all these codes

code.name: Required Binding
code.description: This value set is used as a required binding (in addition to the base binding (not a replacement), usually in a particular usage context)

code.name: Conformance Binding
code.description: This value set is used as an extensible binding (in addition to the base binding (not a replacement), usually in a particular usage context)

code.name: Candidate Binding
code.description: This value set is a candidate to substitute for the overall conformance value set in some situations; usually these are defined in the documentation

code.name: Current Binding
code.description: New records are required to use this value set, but legacy records may use other codes. The definition of 'new record' is difficult, since systems often create new records based on pre-existing data. Usually 'current' bindings are mandated by an external authority that makes clear rules around this

code.name: Preferred Binding
code.description: This is the value set that is preferred in a given context (documentation should explain why)

code.name: UI Suggested Binding
code.description: This value set is provided for user look up in a given context. Typically, these valuesets only include a subset of codes relevant for input in a context

code.name: Starter Binding
code.description: This value set is a good set of codes to start with when designing your system

code.name: Component Binding
code.description: This value set is a component of the base value set. Usually this is called out so that documentation can be written about a portion of the value set

codeset.name: ContactPointSystem
codeset.description: Telecommunications form for contact point.

code.name: Phone
code.description: The value is a telephone number used for voice calls. Use of full international numbers starting with + is recommended to enable automatic dialing support but not required.

code.name: Fax
code.description: The value is a fax machine. Use of full international numbers starting with + is recommended to enable automatic dialing support but not required.

code.name: Email
code.description: The value is an email address.

code.name: Pager
code.description: The value is a pager number. These may be local pager numbers that are only usable on a particular pager system.

code.name: URL
code.description: A contact that is not a phone, fax, pager or email address and is expressed as a URL. This is intended for various institutional or personal contacts including web sites, blogs, Skype, Twitter, Facebook, etc. Do not use for email addresses.

code.name: SMS
code.description: A contact that can be used for sending a sms message (e.g. mobile phones, some landlines).

code.name: Other
code.description: A contact that is not a phone, fax, page or email address and is not expressible as a URL. E.g. Internal mail address. This SHOULD NOT be used for contacts that are expressible as a URL (e.g. Skype, Twitter, Facebook, etc.) Extensions may be used to distinguish "other" contact types.

codeset.name: EventTiming
codeset.description: Real-world event relating to the schedule.

code.name: Morning
code.description: Event occurs during the morning. The exact time is unspecified and established by institution convention or patient interpretation.

code.name: Early Morning
code.description: Event occurs during the early morning. The exact time is unspecified and established by institution convention or patient interpretation.

code.name: Late Morning
code.description: Event occurs during the late morning. The exact time is unspecified and established by institution convention or patient interpretation.

code.name: Noon
code.description: Event occurs around 12:00pm. The exact time is unspecified and established by institution convention or patient interpretation.

code.name: Afternoon
code.description: Event occurs during the afternoon. The exact time is unspecified and established by institution convention or patient interpretation.

code.name: Early Afternoon
code.description: Event occurs during the early afternoon. The exact time is unspecified and established by institution convention or patient interpretation.

code.name: Late Afternoon
code.description: Event occurs during the late afternoon. The exact time is unspecified and established by institution convention or patient interpretation.

code.name: Evening
code.description: Event occurs during the evening. The exact time is unspecified and established by institution convention or patient interpretation.

code.name: Early Evening
code.description: Event occurs during the early evening. The exact time is unspecified and established by institution convention or patient interpretation.

code.name: Late Evening
code.description: Event occurs during the late evening. The exact time is unspecified and established by institution convention or patient interpretation.

code.name: Night
code.description: Event occurs during the night. The exact time is unspecified and established by institution convention or patient interpretation.

code.name: After Sleep
code.description: Event occurs [offset] after subject goes to sleep. The exact time is unspecified and established by institution convention or patient interpretation.

code.name: Immediate
code.description: Event occurs a single time (with no repetitions) as soon as possible after the scheduled or actual start of the overall event.

codeset.name: NarrativeStatus
codeset.description: The status of a resource narrative.

code.name: Generated
code.description: The contents of the narrative are entirely generated from the core elements in the content.

code.name: Extensions
code.description: The contents of the narrative are entirely generated from the core elements in the content and some of the content is generated from extensions. The narrative SHALL reflect the impact of all modifier extensions.

code.name: Additional
code.description: The contents of the narrative may contain additional information not found in the structured data. Note that there is no computable way to determine what the extra information is, other than by human inspection.

code.name: Empty
code.description: The contents of the narrative are some equivalent of "No human-readable text provided in this case".

codeset.name: DaysOfWeek
codeset.description: The days of the week.

code.name: Monday
code.description: Monday.

code.name: Tuesday
code.description: Tuesday.

code.name: Wednesday
code.description: Wednesday.

code.name: Thursday
code.description: Thursday.

code.name: Friday
code.description: Friday.

code.name: Saturday
code.description: Saturday.

code.name: Sunday
code.description: Sunday.

codeset.name: TimingAbbreviation
codeset.description: Code for a known / defined timing pattern.

code.name: Continuous (frequency)
code.description: Service is provided continuously between start time and stop time.

codeset.name: ContributorType
codeset.description: The type of contributor.

code.name: Author
code.description: An author of the content of the module.

code.name: Editor
code.description: An editor of the content of the module.

code.name: Reviewer
code.description: A reviewer of the content of the module.

code.name: Endorser
code.description: An endorser of the content of the module.

codeset.name: IdentifierUse
codeset.description: Identifies the purpose for this identifier, if known .

code.name: Usual
code.description: The identifier recommended for display and use in real-world interactions which should be used when such identifier is different from the "official" identifier.

code.name: Official
code.description: The identifier considered to be most trusted for the identification of this item. Sometimes also known as "primary" and "main". The determination of "official" is subjective and implementation guides often provide additional guidelines for use.

code.name: Temp
code.description: A temporary identifier.

code.name: Secondary
code.description: An identifier that was assigned in secondary use - it serves to identify the object in a relative context, but cannot be consistently assigned to the same object again in a different context.

code.name: Old
code.description: The identifier id no longer considered valid, but may be relevant for search purposes. E.g. Changes to identifier schemes, account merges, etc.

codeset.name: DiscriminatorType
codeset.description: How an element value is interpreted when discrimination is evaluated.

code.name: Value
code.description: The slices have different values in the nominated element, as determined by the applicable fixed value, pattern, or required ValueSet binding.

code.name: Exists
code.description: The slices are differentiated by the presence or absence of the nominated element. There SHALL be no more than two slices. The slices are differentiated by the fact that one must have a max of 0 and the other must have a min of 1 (or more). The order in which the slices are declared doesn't matter.

code.name: Pattern
code.description: The slices have different values in the nominated element, as determined by the applicable fixed value, pattern, or required ValueSet binding. This has the same meaning as 'value' and is deprecated.

code.name: Type
code.description: The slices are differentiated by type of the nominated element.

code.name: Profile
code.description: The slices are differentiated by conformance of the nominated element to a specified profile. Note that if the path specifies .resolve() then the profile is the target profile on the reference. In this case, validation by the possible profiles is required to differentiate the slices.

code.name: Position
code.description: The slices are differentiated by their index. This is only possible if all but the last slice have min=max cardinality, and the (optional) last slice contains other undifferentiated elements.

codeset.name: TriggerType
codeset.description: The type of trigger.

code.name: Named Event
code.description: The trigger occurs in response to a specific named event, and no other information about the trigger is specified. Named events are completely pre-coordinated, and the formal semantics of the trigger are not provided.

code.name: Periodic
code.description: The trigger occurs at a specific time or periodically as described by a timing or schedule. A periodic event cannot have any data elements, but may have a name assigned as a shorthand for the event.

code.name: Data Changed
code.description: The trigger occurs whenever data of a particular type is changed in any way, either added, modified, or removed.

code.name: Data Accessed
code.description: The trigger occurs whenever data of a particular type is accessed.

code.name: Data Access Ended
code.description: The trigger occurs whenever access to data of a particular type is completed.

codeset.name: SortDirection
codeset.description: The possible sort directions, ascending or descending.

code.name: Ascending
code.description: Sort by the value ascending, so that lower values appear first.

code.name: Descending
code.description: Sort by the value descending, so that lower values appear last.

codeset.name: RelatedArtifactType
codeset.description: The type of relationship to the related artifact.

code.name: Documentation
code.description: Additional documentation for the knowledge resource. This would include additional instructions on usage as well as additional information on clinical context or appropriateness.

code.name: Justification
code.description: The target artifact is a summary of the justification for the knowledge resource including supporting evidence, relevant guidelines, or other clinically important information. This information is intended to provide a way to make the justification for the knowledge resource available to the consumer of interventions or results produced by the knowledge resource.

code.name: Citation
code.description: Bibliographic citation for papers, references, or other relevant material for the knowledge resource. This is intended to allow for citation of related material, but that was not necessarily specifically prepared in connection with this knowledge resource.

code.name: Predecessor
code.description: The previous version of the knowledge artifact, used to establish an ordering of versions of an artifact, independent of the status of each version.

code.name: Successor
code.description: The subsequent version of the knowledge artfact, used to establish an ordering of versions of an artifact, independent of the status of each version.

code.name: Derived From
code.description: This artifact is derived from the target artifact. This is intended to capture the relationship in which a particular knowledge resource is based on the content of another artifact, but is modified to capture either a different set of overall requirements, or a more specific set of requirements such as those involved in a particular institution or clinical setting. The artifact may be derived from one or more target artifacts.

code.name: Depends On
code.description: This artifact depends on the target artifact. There is a requirement to use the target artifact in the creation or interpretation of this artifact.

code.name: Composed Of
code.description: This artifact is composed of the target artifact. This artifact is constructed with the target artifact as a component. The target artifact is a part of this artifact. (A dataset is composed of data.).

code.name: Part Of
code.description: This artifact is a part of the target artifact. The target artifact is composed of this artifact (and possibly other artifacts).

code.name: Amends
code.description: This artifact amends or changes the target artifact. This artifact adds additional information that is functionally expected to replace information in the target artifact. This artifact replaces a part but not all of the target artifact.

code.name: Amended With
code.description: This artifact is amended with or changed by the target artifact. There is information in this artifact that should be functionally replaced with information in the target artifact.

code.name: Appends
code.description: This artifact adds additional information to the target artifact. The additional information does not replace or change information in the target artifact.

code.name: Appended With
code.description: This artifact has additional information in the target artifact.

code.name: Cites
code.description: This artifact cites the target artifact. This may be a bibliographic citation for papers, references, or other relevant material for the knowledge resource. This is intended to allow for citation of related material, but that was not necessarily specifically prepared in connection with this knowledge resource.

code.name: Cited By
code.description: This artifact is cited by the target artifact.

code.name: Is Comment On
code.description: This artifact contains comments about the target artifact.

code.name: Has Comment In
code.description: This artifact has comments about it in the target artifact. The type of comments may be expressed in the targetClassifier element such as reply, review, editorial, feedback, solicited, unsolicited, structured, unstructured.

code.name: Contains
code.description: This artifact is a container in which the target artifact is contained. A container is a data structure whose instances are collections of other objects. (A database contains the dataset.).

code.name: Contained In
code.description: This artifact is contained in the target artifact. The target artifact is a data structure whose instances are collections of other objects.

code.name: Corrects
code.description: This artifact identifies errors and replacement content for the target artifact.

code.name: Correction In
code.description: This artifact has corrections to it in the target artifact. The target artifact identifies errors and replacement content for this artifact.

code.name: Replaces
code.description: This artifact replaces or supersedes the target artifact. The target artifact may be considered deprecated.

code.name: Replaced With
code.description: This artifact is replaced with or superseded by the target artifact. This artifact may be considered deprecated.

code.name: Retracts
code.description: This artifact retracts the target artifact. The content that was published in the target artifact should be considered removed from publication and should no longer be considered part of the public record.

code.name: Retracted By
code.description: This artifact is retracted by the target artifact. The content that was published in this artifact should be considered removed from publication and should no longer be considered part of the public record.

code.name: Signs
code.description: This artifact is a signature of the target artifact.

code.name: Similar To
code.description: This artifact has characteristics in common with the target artifact. This relationship may be used in systems to "deduplicate" knowledge artifacts from different sources, or in systems to show "similar items".

code.name: Supports
code.description: This artifact provides additional support for the target artifact. The type of support is not documentation as it does not describe, explain, or instruct regarding the target artifact.

code.name: Supported With
code.description: The target artifact contains additional information related to the knowledge artifact but is not documentation as the additional information does not describe, explain, or instruct regarding the knowledge artifact content or application. This could include an associated dataset.

code.name: Transforms
code.description: This artifact was generated by transforming the target artifact (e.g., format or language conversion). This is intended to capture the relationship in which a particular knowledge resource is based on the content of another artifact, but changes are only apparent in form and there is only one target artifact with the "transforms" relationship type.

code.name: Transformed Into
code.description: This artifact was transformed into the target artifact (e.g., by format or language conversion).

code.name: Transformed With
code.description: This artifact was generated by transforming a related artifact (e.g., format or language conversion), noted separately with the "transforms" relationship type. This transformation used the target artifact to inform the transformation. The target artifact may be a conversion script or translation guide.

code.name: Documents
code.description: This artifact provides additional documentation for the target artifact. This could include additional instructions on usage as well as additional information on clinical context or appropriateness.

code.name: Specification Of
code.description: The target artifact is a precise description of a concept in this artifact. This may be used when the RelatedArtifact datatype is used in elements contained in this artifact.

code.name: Created With
code.description: This artifact was created with the target artifact. The target artifact is a tool or support material used in the creation of the artifact, and not content that the artifact was derived from.

code.name: Cite As
code.description: The related artifact is the citation for this artifact.
